column1:
rain shower
from the gutters:
crickets

graying sky soaring;
a roof above the heads of
mortal creatures beneath

the smell of wet earth
streetlight halos in the rain;
yukatta raincoat

no washrooms anywhere;
crouching behind a tree
i can hear everything now

prize chrysanthemum
you have written your own haiku;
you don't need mine

light from the snow;
my wife shows me a small bloom
on the hyacinth

reading by lamplight;
sounds of a summer night
press against the screen

steady autumn wind;
balloons at the same slant
in a used-car lot

damp spring evening;
body smells
of the home-coming dog

higginson's haiku
still among the living;
the autumn wind

calder sculpture;
a single brown leaf tumbling
from the sky

sent outside
while the old women talk:
scent of sweetpeas

fresh snow
for the hands,
for the face

if onlys,
what ifs??
twilight

easter sunrise;
gun towers overshadow
the prison graveyard

becalmed;
a blue butterfly
clings to the sail

the indignant cat
has turned its back on me;
ticking clock

november wanes;
the farmer's pet gander
honks at the moon

i open my eyes
from dreams to daydreams:
whirligig beetle
